o cannot admit a mistake by their own or forgive a mistake of others, people who cannot share or put down their greed.<br><br>Personally I am happy if I can learn something, even if I have to admit a mistake (it may take some time until I understand that I did something wrong though), I have stepped back from lottoing on items others have more use of, I am happy to follow other, more experienced players if they lead me through unknown places or events. And I have given up camps if someone else started to hunt there too and there were not enough spawns for both of us - after asking that person to leave of course. I would do the same if I were raidleader of my guild and someone else is in the zone we intended to raid before we could be there.<br><br>On the same behalf I don't understand how people allways can run into problems with others, having real deep hate establish from those problems. People who start their own personal warfares because of this and not even caring about if they destroy others players fun in the game (e.g. by recruiting from the guild they just left). Never - except the shortterm issue that ended in an appology - happened something like that to me. People like or respect me a lot, the ones that get into trouble with others all the time as well as the ones whom people get into trouble with constantly. Is it <br>...because I respect them? <br>...because I talk to them like with adults, appealing to their maturity and coolness if needed? <br>...because I respect their wishes and also help them to accomplish them - even if it means to leave my camp/group/quest/whatever sometimes?<br><br>Please don't get me wrong, there is a gleam of greed in my eyes (when it comes to my epic quest), there are equivocal words coming from my lips (if I have a bad day or moment), and I have nearly no comprehension for begging or exorbitant lazyness. So I am no perfect person by any means, but how, please tell me, can it be that there evolves so much trouble, hate and envy between people all the time?<br><br>Thank you for listening to me, and sorry if I spammed this board with senseless or obsolete stuff.<br><br><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.elvenkingdomguild.org/memberpics/shayariel_logo.jpg"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFF8DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub18.ezboard.com/ukookietherogue.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kookie the rogue</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://users.rcn.com/sovereignz/banana.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>MMDN Mascot</span><br>  Posts: 411<br> <font color=#006400>(12/18/01 5:51:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub18.ezboard.com/fmithanielmarrdailynewsfrm40.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=142.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://users.rcn.com/sovereignz/banana.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_blush.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: I think I am lucky...</span><hr size=1> You arent lucky. You just have respect and a lil bit of common sense unlike some flamers here <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#DEEFDE><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub18.ezboard.com/upaluwen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Paluwen </A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>MithMarr Squire</span><br>  Posts: 50<br> <font color=#006400>(12/18/01 7:21:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub18.ezboard.com/fmithanielmarrdailynewsfrm40.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=142.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_blush.gif" align=absmiddle>  /clap</span><hr size=1> True....I'm sure your post strikes true with a large majority of players. Unfortunately they probably arent the ones who post here, although they probably read the posts here like most do. I'm sure it has occured to most everyone that the ones who whine, complain, flame and string long threads of almost undecipherable bull, do it because they enjoy it. There is a large niche of EQ players who enjoy the high drama caused by that sort of thing and will jump aboard any bandwagon carrying it, which is why boards like these swell with rants &amp; flames. The really sad part of it is, some of them take it to the extreme inside the game.<br><br>So, take a look at those with a post on almost every rant or flame thread and compare that to how often you've ever seen them inside the game somewhere exploring or hunting. Then see how many of them you find in NFP or one of the overcamped, train-a-minute zones most likely at the head of the biggest train themselves. <br><br>There's a whole EQ society alive in the boards of people who don't even play EQ anymore and people who rarely play at all. Also, theres a lot of people with little or no experiences of their own in the game. So, again, take a look at whose flaming or whining and think again when the last time you saw them in game and what their reputation is if they've been around a while. I doubt you'd care much about their opinion after that.<br><br>I have nothing against the rant boards, in fact I love to read them for a laugh while im in some kind of downtime in a camp or raid, like now. Ive also posted sometimes mostly to amuse myself or /wave at a friend or to express an opinion like now (although very little of the latter).<br><br>I personally, like you, havent really had anything to complain about in-game, and certainly nothing that should matter to anyone else. I have at worst been ticked off by someone who screams endlessly in OOC or Shout about someone else they don't like or a situation that upset them. Yeah OOC is out-of-character